data.content:
**Yes, C# fully supports `stackalloc`'d `Span<nint>` and `Span<nuint>`.** Here's what works:

```csharp
Span<nint> span = stackalloc nint[4];
Span<nuint> uspan = stackalloc nuint[3];
```

The test confirms both compile and run correctly. Under the hood, `nint` maps to `IntPtr` and `nuint` maps to `UIntPtr`. This has been supported since C# 9 (which introduced `nint`/`nuint` as first-class numeric types) combined with the `stackalloc` in `Span<T>` feature from C# 7.2+.
